name: TOI-150
scenarioDescription:
The TOI-150 Exoplanetary System


Overview

TOI-150 is a star with 1.35 times the mass of the Sun, and 1.53 times its radius. It is located 1095.88 light years away from the solar system and is estimated to be 2.346 billion years old, as compared to the Sun which is roughly 4.6 billion years old.

TOI-150 is known to have 1 exoplanets in orbit around it.


Exoplanets in the TOI-150 system


TOI-150 b

TOI-150 b was discovered by the Transiting Exoplanet Survey Satellite (TESS) observatory using the transit method. Its semi-major axis is 0.07 astronomical units, as compared to Earth's which is 1 astronomical unit. The mass of TOI-150 b is 798.18 times the mass of Earth. The radius of TOI-150 b is 14.067 that of Earth. At more than 50 Earth masses, TOI-150 b is a gas giant, a planet whose mass is mostly made up of hydrogen and helium, like Jupiter and Saturn in our solar system.
description: 3D visualisation and gravity simulation of the exoplanet system TOI-150, which contains 1 planets and was discovered by Transiting Exoplanet Survey Satellite (TESS).
